          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row j5" id="Social">
          <div class="head-3">
            <h3>6. Communications</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="md-space">
            <h4 class="xs-space">Social Media</h4>
            <div class="xs-space">When conducting research, social media was identified as an important aspect of marketing furniture and home products. Given the limited resources for this project, I developed a social media strategy that would take advantage of the images we already had and content that would help develop the site at the same time. I built our strategy around "content pillars" and leaned heavily into our brand "why"which for us was about Designers, Craftsmanship, and Process. I arranged and conducted interviews with the designers in order to create profiles and quotable content, planned and photographed process and detail shots of our products, and created and maintained a visual style for our social media content.
            </div>
            <div class="xs-space half-content">
              <img src="/assets/images/igmockup-gray.png" />
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="md-space">
            <h4 class="xs-space">Product Photography</h4>
            <div>My responsibilities for the site included product photography for each furniture and art item. I had no professional experience in photography before this, but after some practice it became a favorite part of my job. I was responsible for planning shoots, setting up lighting, editing multiple views for each piece, and uploading the new photos to sales platforms.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="md-space">
            <h4 class="xs-space">Print Design</h4>
            <div class="xs-space">There were a number of printed assets needed for Signature Pick, including tearsheets, business cards and mailer postcards.</div>
            <div class="row">
              <div class="half-content col-sm-6">
                <img src="/assets/images/sigpick-ts1.png" />
